Module me.sbasalaev.tybyco
Package me.sbasalaev.tybyco.builders

Interface CodeBlockBuilder<Result>

All Superinterfaces:
CodeBuilder<Result>
public interface CodeBlockBuilder<Result> extends CodeBuilder<Result>
Builder of a code block of a method or constructor.

Stack checks

The builder checks that the values on stack are at least of a correct TypeKind. In doing so it even distinguishes between boolean, byte, char, short and int. The numeric types byte, char and short are widened to int as needed but the narrowing conversion must be explicit. To convert between numeric types use numericCast(). There is no conversion between an int and a boolean.

invokespecial and invokeinterface

There are no matching methods for invokespecial and invokeinterface instructions. Instead, the correct instruction is selected based on a class reference, target Java version and the intention:
  • Use invokeConstructor() to call a constructor.
  • Use invokeStatic() to call a static method of a class or interface.
  • use invokeVirtual() to call a non-private instance method of a class or interface.
  • use invokePrivate() to call a private instance method of a class or interface.
  • use invokeSuper() to call an instance method of a superclass or superinterface.

    • add

      CodeBlockBuilder<Result> add()
      Writes appropriate instruction to add two numbers on the stack. The top of the stack must contain two values of the same numeric type. If either of values is of type byte, char or short it is promoted to int.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the stack has less than two values or the values are not the same numeric type.

    • open

      CodeBlockBuilder<Result> open(LocalVar local)
      Adds new local variable to the scope of the method but does not assign it. This method does not write any instructions but reserves a slot for the local and allows it to be assigned later by store(me.sbasalaev.tybyco.builders.LocalVar). This is most useful for variables with discontinuous assigned range.

    • close

      CodeBlockBuilder<Result> close(LocalVar local)
      Removes given variable from the scope of this method. This method frees the slot occupied by the variable. If the variable is not anonymous it also adds entries for LocalVariableTable, LocalVariableTypeTable and type annotations on the type of the variable.

    • numericCast

      CodeBlockBuilder<Result> numericCast(JvmPrimitiveType toType)
      Writes instructions to convert the number on the stack to given type. The effect is exactly the same as the corresponding numeric type cast in Java, e.g. if the top of the stack is n then 
      numericCast(JvmPrimitiveType.BYTE)
      is equivalent to Java code 
      (byte) n
      The method may end up writing no instructions (e.g. when n is already a byte) or writing more than one (e.g. D2I, I2B when n is double).
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if toType is not a numeric type.
      IllegalStateException - if the type on the stack is not a numeric one.

    • jumpIfCmp

      CodeBlockBuilder<Result> jumpIfCmp(Cmp cmp, Target target)
      Writes conditional jump on comparison. The jump occures if the comparison of two values on the stack yields given comparison result. The two values must be of the same TypeKind. If either of values is byte, char or short it is promoted to int. If values are boolean or of reference types then only Cmp.EQ and Cmp.NE are allowed.
      Parameters:
      cmp - the expected result of comparison.
      target - target instruction to jump to.

    • jumpIfCmpZero

      CodeBlockBuilder<Result> jumpIfCmpZero(Cmp cmp, Target target)
      Writes conditional jump on comparison with integer zero. The jump occures if the comparison of the value on the stack with zero yields given result. The value on the stack must be one of byte, char, short or int.
      Parameters:
      cmp - the expected result of comparison with zero.
      target - target instruction to jump to.

    • jumpIfCmpNull

      CodeBlockBuilder<Result> jumpIfCmpNull(Cmp cmp, Target target)
      Writes conditional jump on comparison with null. The jump occures if the comparison of the value on the stack with null yields given comparison result. The value on the stack must be of reference type. Only Cmp.EQ and Cmp.NE are allowed as comparison results.
      Parameters:
      cmp - the expected result of comparison with null, either Cmp.EQ or Cmp.NE.
      target - target instruction to jump to.

    • jumpSwitch

      CodeBuilder<Result> jumpSwitch(Map<Integer,Target> keyTargets, Target dfltTarget)
      Writes switch instruction and ends the current block of code. The switch instruction takes int key from the stack and jumps to the target that matches the key or to the dfltTarget if none match. The method automatically chooses between TABLESWITCH and LOOKUPSWITCH instructions choosing the one that is shorter.
      Parameters:
      keyTargets - map from integer keys to target instructions.
      dfltTarget - the target if no keys match.

    • athrow

      CodeBuilder<Result> athrow()
      Writes athrow instruction and ends the current block of code. athrow throws exception pushed on the top of the stack.

    • atTryCatch

      default CodeBlockBuilder<Result> atTryCatch(Target end, Target catchHandler, JvmClassType... exceptionTypes)
      Marks current position as the start of try/catch block for given exception types. This is a convenient variadic form of atTryCatch(me.sbasalaev.tybyco.builders.Target, me.sbasalaev.tybyco.builders.Target, me.sbasalaev.collection.List) and has the same semantics.
      Parameters:
      end - target position at which this try block ends.
      catchHandler - target position at which catch block starts.
      exceptionTypes - exceptions types that are caught by this try block.

    • atTryCatch

      CodeBlockBuilder<Result> atTryCatch(Target end, Target catchHandler, List<JvmClassType> exceptionTypes)
      Marks current position as the start of try/catch block for given exception types. The end and catchHandler must mark target instructions further in the code, i.e. not already visited by CodeBuilder.at(me.sbasalaev.tybyco.builders.Target). If no exceptions are given this block catches all exceptions. Such blocks are used to implement finally. This method also writes type annotations for the exception types.
      Parameters:
      end - target position at which this try block ends.
      catchHandler - target position at which catch block starts.
      exceptionTypes - exceptions types that are caught by this try block.
